{
  "stem": "16345.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But to show you that even after the war I was afraid to appear Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I went back to Poland, and I found out that Przytyk didn't exist anymore.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the town next to it, which was about 10 miles away, Radom, which was a substantial town--",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "R-A-D-O-M.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Radom was the closest town to it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I finally found an aunt of mine-- my Aunt Bela, my mother's younger sister.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She had been so-- sort of mutilated during the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She had lost an eye and several toes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was in bad shape, but at least I found somebody.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And at the time the Russians were all over Poland, and Pol-- Poland had a communist government.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I tried to get some of our stuff-- some of our things back from some farmers, those farmer friends of ours near Przytyk.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the first thing they say when they see me and I say I am-- I am Henry Aizenman, the small Aizenman, they look at me like I was some kind of an-- a wild animal.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They said [NON-ENGLISH], which means little Aizenman, you're still alive-- with surprise.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then they start telling me that the Germans took everything away that we had left with them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, the way they were looking at me, they were looking at me like-- like you look at a turkey around Thanksgiving.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I-- I got out of there in a hurry.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I said, there's nothing to be gained from this, and I went back to Radom.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And after several weeks in Radom-- that was already the end of 1945, towards the end of 1945.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And an incident occurred in Radom.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
